  "ticket": {
    "acceptance": {
      "assertions": [
        "VenvStoreVersionsAreContentAddressed, VenvStoreLatestIsStored, VenvStoreLatestUniquePerUnit hold in TLC over the current model.",
        "Installing the same unit at two shas leaves both store entries and exactly one latest pointer.",
        "RemoveUnit leaves store entries intact (cache semantics)."
      ],
      "deviations": [
        "The objective says 'every install/sync records the unit's content'. The TLA+ models StoreUnitVersion as a separate action on an already-installed unit (InstallUnitImpl and RemoveUnitImpl both leave project_model unchanged), so the implementation follows the model, not the prose: a distinct `store add` CLI surface. Install/sync are untouched. Two hazards this sidesteps \u2014 the sha is unknown at install time for file:/registry sources (InstalledUnit.gitHash is only set for Kind.GIT), and SyncGitHandler merges into the working copy in place, which an immutable snapshot cannot absorb.",
        "latest/ is a real directory, not a symlink into a snapshot, for the same in-place-merge reason.",
        "The store covers skills only. Plugins, doc-repos, and harness templates keep the flat layout; the model has no kind dimension, so this is under-specification rather than a spec violation. Tracked separately \u2014 it blocks a coherent SMVENV-002, which pins 'units'."
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "TLC over ticket current/: all 7 configs clean; InternalVenvCases 109,621 states / 2,610 distinct / depth 11; the three Venv store invariants hold.",
        "spec-unit: 2 targets pass (17 + 21 cases), incl. tests/test_store_projection.py pinning observe_home against the store layout.",
        "repo unit tests: jbang RunTests.java ALL PASSED; new ContentAddressedStoreTest (9 cases).",
        "test graph: 19 graphs green. specExternalPhase could not run (pre-existing testgraphsdk ImportError) \u2014 the ticket's named graph_after_unit_pass is unproven; see the specExternalPhase issue.",
        "manual end-to-end CLI: install -> store add x2 -> remove; both snapshots and the latest marker survive removal; store add on a removed-but-snapshotted unit still rejects UNIT_NOT_INSTALLED."
      ]
    },
